Regression test for the worked example in
`saw-core-lean/doc/getting-started.md`.

The doc walks a user through emitting a Cryptol property as a Lean
goal via `offline_lean`, setting up a Lake project, and discharging
the goal with a short tactic proof. This test file holds that
proof verbatim and asserts it elaborates cleanly. If the iteDep/ite
wrappers stop being `@[reducible]`, or the SpecialTreatment
routing changes, or any other regression breaks the tactic — this
test fails loud.

The test driver is bespoke (pure Lean, no SAW involvement) and
mirrors the test_lean_soundness_*_prop pattern.
